reviews.text: These will be going back as soon as I get replacements and pull the ones I've installed back out. They have a 4.7 rating as I write this, so perhaps I just got a bad batch, but bad they are. I've installed 3 of these so far with a 100% defective rate. Each works only intermittently. I had originally stopped after the 1st one was acting up straight out of the box. For that one, over 2-3 days, it went from sometimes working, to mostly working, to ok, I think it works now, to still refusing to switch on sometimes. The 2nd two have been more definitively in the "switch it on and see if it works...". If it doesn't, you can flip it 100 times and it still won't. Then, minutes or hours later it may decide it is finally ready to turn on after all. In the attached video taken by my wife, I believe she is flipping the switch, it is flashing on for a moment and then going out, and then she is cycling the switch again and getting the same result. All lights on that switch circuit are in sync, so it isn't just the one light shown. I have wired perhaps 300-500 switches/sockets/etc in my day and never seen this kind of behavior. In general, switches are sort of a "they work or they don't" thing. If they don't work they stay not working. If they are flakey, they are flakey in a consistent way (usually from a marginal contact). I didn't actually need a full box and just went for it as I do have some other non-LED compatible electronic 3-way dimmers I could swap and the box price was less than 4 switches. Given the rating, I've considered an exchange, but probably will just go grab a few from the hardware store. If I exchange and a new box of these works, I'll update this review.
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.title: So far, a 100% defective rate...

reviews.text: I know my kids aren't the easiest on light switches. Because after 10+ years of use, a few of our house's original rocker switches broke and I needed to replace them. I tried these Enerlites as replacements and every single one (10+) broke within 3 months of use. Their design is horribly flawed. They work when you test them but the pivot for the rocker is a tiny piece of weak plastic that fails with even relatively gentle but regular use. I've rarely been so utterly dissatisfied with a product. I have resorted to using ugly but durable traditional toggle switches simply because this product has shaken my faith that I can find a semi-reliable rocker style switch again. AVOID!
